A fire whose cause is yet to be established has gutted the Busia County finance offices. Interestingly, the Wednesday 2am incident happened in the vicinity of a multimillion shillings fire engine that is usually parked at the county headquarters. Busia County Communications Director Winnstone Mbada said they are yet to establish the cause of the fire. "The situation has been controlled. We are working closely with relevant authorities to establish the cause of the fire," Mr Mbada told the Nation.  More follows...  